p.value: On Davis sent a gift of his papers on squatters' rights in 2006. The accession number associated with this gift is 2006.021.
On Davis was involved in the 1980s squatters' rights movement in New York City's East Village which culminated in the Tompkins Square Park Police Riot of August 1988.

physdesc.value: Some of the newspapers in this flat box (18" x 14" x 3") are oversized and folded, and must be handled with care. Brittle items cannot be handled without prior permission of Library staff.

p.value: The collection consists of subject files, clippings, oversized artwork, account books and a diary composed by squatters at 537 East 13th Street.

Copyright (and related rights to publicity and privacy) to materials in this collection created by On Davis was not transferred to New York University. Permission to use materials must be secured from the copyright holder.
